BombCustomMessages.ttks:
Turn the Keys is a module on this bomb. It dictates some modules be delayed until others are finished. Until Turn the Keys is finished, you should avoid doing the following modules:
Left Key: Maze, Memory, Complicated Wires, Wire Sequence, Cryptography
Right Key: Simon Says, Semaphore, Combination Lock, Astrology, Switches, Plumbing
BombCustomMessages.ttksleft:
These modules need to be solved: Password, Who's on First, Keypad, Crazy Talk, Listening, Orientation Cube.
Avoid solving these modules: Maze, Memory, Complicated Wires, Wire Sequences, Cryptography.
Left Key is turned from Low to High.
BombCustomMessages.ttksright:
These modules need to be solved: Morse Code, Wires, The Button, Two Bits, Colour Flash, Round Keypad.
Avoid solving these modules: Simon Says, Semaphore, Combination Lock, Astrology, Switches, Plumbing.
Right Key is turned from High to Low.
BombCustomMessages.infozen: Zen Mode is a peaceful mode. The clock counts up instead of down. Strikes can't blow up the bomb (though they still count). Points are reduced by 75%. Use the time given by !bomb time for starting time calculations.
BombCustomMessages.qhelp: A solve queue is generally used when a Forget Everything or similar boss module is present on the bomb. To add a command to the queue, type “!q” before your command (ex. “!q !1 submit”). You can name a command by typing “!q [name]” before your command (ex. “!q 12 solves !1 submit” will be named “12 solves” and will run “!1 submit” when called). To remove something from the queue, use “!unq !1” for commands concerning module 1 and “!unq 12 solved” for named commands. Use “!listq” to see your items in the queue or “!listqall” for everybody's. See “!callhelp” for how to manage a queue.
BombCustomMessages.infotraining: Training Mode is a peaceful mode designed for practicing unfamilar modules. The clock counts up instead of down. Strikes can't blow up the bomb (though they still count). Points are nullified, and if you don't like the modules, you can !newbomb to get new ones. Use the time given by !bomb time for starting time calculations. Be aware of the time you have to practice (if enabled)!
BombCustomMessages.callhelp: If you are the player running the solve queue, use “!call” to run the next unnamed command from the queue. You may also use “!call [name]” to run a named command (ex. “!call 12 solves”). Use “!callall” to call every command in the queue. For multiple callers, use “!callset #” to specify how many. See “!qhelp” on how to queue.
BombCustomMessages.fml: Forget Me Later, or FML for short requires an interaction inbetween every solve. The user must grab every digit before the first solve otherwise blind guesses will be a problem. Refer to “!qhelp” on how to queue for this module.
BombCustomMessages.organ: Organization requires a specific module to be solved for every instance present. Solving a different module not accounted by Organization will cause strikes. Refer to “!qhelp” on how to queue for this module.

GeneralCustomMessages.welcome: Welcome, this is a Twitch Plays version of Keep Talking and Nobody Explodes. For some basic info and how to get started, check the help message for this game.
GeneralCustomMessages.ktane: Keep Talking and Nobody Explodes is developed by Steel Crate Games. It's available for Windows PC, Mac OS X, PlayStation VR, Samsung Gear VR and Google Daydream. See http://www.keeptalkinggame.com/ for more information!
GeneralCustomMessages.about: Twitch Plays: KTaNE is an alternative way of playing !ktane. Unlike the original game, you play as both defuser and expert, and defuse the bomb by sending special commands to the chat. Try !help for more information!
GeneralCustomMessages.discord: The official KTaNE Discord can be found here: https://discord.gg/ktane
GeneralCustomMessages.tpdiscord: The KTaNE TP Discord can be found here: https://discord.gg/CYVWy3n
GeneralCustomMessages.ircimg: This image on the irc manager was created by ししく. The link to the original image is here: https://www.pixiv.net/en/artworks/84089169
GeneralCustomMessages.dmghelp: With “!dmg run”, you can run custom bombs. Specify “ALL_SOLVABLES” if you want any modules to show up, “ALL_MODS” to have any modded module show up, etc. Use the repo, https://ktane.timwi.de/, and tick Module ID in the settings to display if you want to run specific modules. See “!dmgvar” for other variables that can be set.
GeneralCustomMessages.dmgvar: Prepending “#*” to any mod ID will add multiples of that. Strike limit can be specified with “#x”, starting time with “#:##”, disable pacing events with “nopacing”, and bring all of the modules to the front with “frontonly” In addition, encasing the module set with “()” will allow for creating multiple bombs at once. Just be sure not to run too many.
GeneralCustomMessages.commands: The list of EVERY single command for TP KTANE can be found here: https://samfundev.github.io/KtaneTwitchPlays/
